    Did a summer internship for HP producing a flash and HTML tutorial showing how to render visualizations of Autodesk Inventor models within 3DS Max.
     
 
\section{Service and Awards}
    I have mentored and advised undergraduate and graduate students at UAB, UMD, and UofU, including: Kyle Headley, Clark Ren, Jiaqing Yuan, Maria Jenkins, Leif Andersen, Javran Cheng, Ph\'uc C. Nguy$\tilde{\textrm{\^e}}$n, and Guannan Wei.

    I have been a reviewer for papers submitted to CC 2013, ICFP 2014, SAS 2015,
    PLDI 2016, and CCS 2017. I have served on the AEC for ECOOP 2018.
    I have served on the PC for IEEE TCBBSI and the SIGPLAN MiniKanren Workshop,
    and am PC chair for the SIGPLAN 20th annual Scheme Workshop.
    I am on the Curriculum Committee at UAB and am co-organizing the High School Programming Contest at UAB. I am faculty advisor to the local ACM student chapter.  

    I won the best student paper award from TFP 2013 for my first publication. With James King, I won the PRACE ISC best paper award for the proceedings
    paper on our new dynamic sparse matrix format \emph{dynamic compressed sparse row} (DCSR). I received the Victor Basili Fellowship lasting two years from the University of Maryland, College Park. 


 
